  stimulus_text = 'The debate on climate change often focuses on the question of whether human activity is the primary driver of climate change.  While many scientists agree that human activity plays a significant role, others believe that natural cycles are the primary driver, and that humans only have a minor impact.  The text suggests that the debate is more complex than a simple binary between human and natural causes. What can be inferred about the author''s perspective on climate change?',
