  stimulus_text = 'In the early 1980s, a group of artists and writers in New York City began to explore the use of digital technology in their work. They called their movement "cyberpunk," and they were interested in the ways in which technology could be used to create new forms of art and literature. They wanted to explore the ways in which technology could be used to create new experiences for the viewer, and they wanted to explore the ways in which technology could be used to create new forms of communication. They believed that technology had the potential to change the way we think about the world, and they wanted to use technology to create new forms of art and literature that reflected these changes.',
